n office chair not going up or down is a fault in the lift mechanism rather than the cylinder itself.";i:7;s:62:"This fix involves two persons but it can be done solo as well.";i:8;s:61:"Get someone to hold down the base of the chair on the ground.";i:9;s:110:"Have another person lift the height lever while pulling the chair up with great force to the highest position.";i:10;s:45:"Once the chair is in the highest position it.";i:11;s:153:"The lever to adjust the height of the seat is always located on the right when seated and towards the front if there is more than one lever on the right.";i:12;s:157:"If your chair has just one lever on the right this single lever will adjust the height of the seat and also lock the backrest in the upright seated position.";i:13;s:33:"These are simple tiltlock chairs.";i:14;s:69:"Pull the lever outwards away from the chair to lock the chair in the.";i:15;s:61:"Get someone to hold down the base of the chair on the ground.";i:16;s:110:"Have another person lift the height lever while pulling the chair up with great force to the highest position.";i:17;s:77:"Once the chair is in the highest position it will begin working as it should.";i:18;s:19:"To lower your seat.";i:19;s:200:"Find the adjustable height leverits usually on the right side of a chair or at the bottom then place your body weight on the chair and push the lever down then it will gradually lower the seat height.";i:20;s:19:"To raise your seat.";i:21;s:121:"Place your body weight to your feet and then pull the height lever up then the chair height will gradually start to rise.";i:22;s:20:"Why is it important.";i:23;s:46:"Sitting down on a chair properly is important.";i:24;s:54:"Generally the best way to tell the proper seat height.";i:25;s:189:"Just keep the seat cushion off until you can press the lever and cause it to move with some weight leaning on the middle and that you actually need to use the lever so its not just sinking.";i:26;s:62:"Pull on the lever until your chair reaches the desired height.";i:27;s:73:"You may need to push the chair down if you want to lower the seat height.";i:28;s:30:"Add Cushions for Added Height.";i:29;s:93:"If your chair still isnt at the height you desire a seat cushion can make up for the deficit.";i:30;s:48:"Just be careful not to get one that is too soft.";i:31;s:84:"A chair cushion that is too soft can lead to you developing an anterior pelvic tilt.";i:32;s:34:"Make sure the cable is not broken.";i:33;s:61:"Remove the cover at the base of the chair and push the lever.";i:34;s:161:"If you see the cable moving the part under the base then the cable is not broken and replacing the cylinder will likely fix the chairs height adjustment problem.";i:35;s:123:"The chair gas lift not working anymore is usually the result of the sealing rings around the piston rod that have worn out.";i:36;s:133:"A lever attached to the chairs gas spring lets the user adjust the chair height by opening or closing the valve and allowing the gas.";i:37;s:103:"This option does not actually repair the office chair but can stop your chair from temporarily sinking.";i:38;s:86:"In order for this method to work the hose clamp must be size 20 or 1316-1-34 diameter.";i:39;s:91:"The hose clamp is placed around the cylinder piston at a desired height and acts as a stop.";i:40;s:95:"Manually turn the seat of the chair clockwise or counter-clockwise to raise and lower the seat.";i:41;s:121:"Depending on the chair itself you will need to turn the seat to see which way is lowering it and which way is raising it.";i:42;s:93:"Once the office chair adjusts sit down to check the height and if it is satisfactory - great.";i:43;s:103:"If your office chair keeps sinking then first check if the external mechanism needs cleaning or oiling.";i:44;s:38:"Sometimes it can be as simple as that.";i:45;s:145:"If that is not the issue then you might have to replace the pneumatic cylinder or the spring that helps with the height adjustment of your chair.";i:46;s:57:"My chairs height wont adjust even when I press the lever.";i:47;s:278:"On several chairs primarily the Steelcase V1 Leap V2 Leap prior to 1192009 and Herman Miller Aeron that use a top activated gas cylinder its common to see a set screw to fine-tune the lever activation of the gas cylinder due to manufacturing tolerances and variations in chairs.";i:48;s:77:"Set the chair height so that the underside of your elbows are at desk height.";i:49;s:112:"If it still doesnt work you may need to look up the manual online and see if there is a troubleshooting section.";i:50;s:111:"Maybe if you look the chair up online you can find an assembly manual that has an image of the lever by itself.";i:51;s:39:"WikiHows Properly adjusting the height.";}}